en_455777_0	The 513 Brigade of the Security Force Headquarters - Jaffna (SFHQ-J) marked its 24th anniversary with a series of programmes, including special religious observances.
en_455777_1	Arrangements were organized on the directions of Colonel Mohammed Fariez, Brigade Commander, 513 Brigade.
en_455777_2	On 28 August, the military formalities commenced with a Guard Turnout, presented by the troops of the 513 Brigade to its Brigade Commander.
en_455777_3	A troop address followed an All-Rank lunch and the planting of a tree sapling in the premises.
en_455777_4	Meanwhile, a Bodhi Pooja and offer of alms also were conducted as part of commemorative ceremonies.
en_455777_5	A simple musical show in the evening on Saturday (31) brought the commemoration to end.
